Package: cicinference
Title: Library of variance estimators in Changes-in-Changes (CiC) design
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Timothée Bacchi [aut, cre]
Authors@R: person("Timothée", "Bacchi", email = "timothee.bacchi@etu.minesparis.psl.eu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Timothée Bacchi <timothee.bacchi@etu.minesparis.psl.eu>
Description: Provides core estimation and inference routines for the empirical
    quantile-based Changes-in-Changes (CiC) counterfactual estimator, defined
    as the average of quantile-transformed ranks. Implements the novel
    asymptotic variance estimators developed by Chhor, D'Haultfoeuille,
    L'Hour, and Mugnier (2026), accommodating both standard independent
    cross-sections and paired panel data configurations. Inference methods
    include full-sample analytical (no-split) plug-in variance estimation,
    sample-splitting techniques, kernel-density-based (KDE) localized
    residual smoothing, and non-parametric bootstrap alternatives (both
    standard-error and percentile intervals). Density estimators utilize a
    user-controlled bandwidth framework with adaptive scaling. Computational
    performance is heavily optimized via 'Rcpp' bindings alongside robust
    input validation and sanitization safeguards.
